column21:
Think back to the very first part of the experiment. Did you notice anything out of the ordinary in the way the words and pictures were presented during the surveillance tasks?

Type your response on the keyboard, it will appear below. 

Press the return/enter key to finish and move on to the next question.

NB You must enter at least 20 characters.
column104: Next to Palpitoad there was a constant association with negative words, meanwhile, Bergmite was always given positive word associations. In addition, Scraggy was associated with fans and concrete while swadloon was also associated with concrete and glass. Bergmite has an icy appearance and that was reinforced with natural landscapes in open shots and even shots of space walks. However, palpitoad's grounded theme was reinforced with close ups of worms and graves. Warm feelings, neutral feelings, and negative feelings were purposefully planted into the participant associations with the creatures. Finally, the target creatures were associated most often with pencils and books or computers, remaining much more neutral.

column21:
Did you notice anything systematic about how particular words and images appeared together during the surveillance tasks?

Type your response on the keyboard, it will appear below. 

Press the return/enter key to finish and move on to the next question.

NB You must enter at least 20 characters.
column104: Concrete and glass appeared frequently together. Images of technology such as the fan and hairdryer appeared together often as well as with the word computer. Pencils and book also appeared together frequently.

column21:
Did you notice anything about the words and images that appeared with certain cartoon creatures? 

Type your response on the keyboard, it will appear below. 

Press the return/enter key to finish and move on to the next question.

NB You must enter at least 20 characters.
column104: Swadloon and Scraggy were kept with neutral words. Swadloon was associated with glass strongly and occassionally concrete. Scraggy was often associated with concrete and images of fans. Swadloon was also associated with pencils and books on occasion. Bergmite was kept with positives and free landscape images. Palpitoad was kept with negative words and images that were often associated with death or the ground.
